   =20
      YOLO
   =20
 =20

In my experience nobody has a more colorful prose style than equity volatil=
ity strategists. There=E2=80=99s something about writing about volatility t=
hat makes your writing volatile? Here=E2=80=99s   Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Tracy=
 Alloway on institutional investors trading short-dated options, quoting Ch=
arlie McElligott, a strategist at Nomura Securities International Inc.:

=E2=80=9CYOLOing into 0 and 1 Days-Til-Expiration (DTE) options has now bee=
n =E2=80=98institutionalized=E2=80=99 by vol traders at many of the largest=
 funds on the Street,=E2=80=9D McElligott wrote in a note to clients. =E2=
=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s not about retail-alone playing this game anymore.=E2=80=
=9D
=E2=80=9CWe have seen witnessed some absolutely biblical usage of 0DTE and =
1DTE options, and it=E2=80=99s acting like jet fuel being dumped on the alr=
eady out of control =E2=80=98macro=E2=80=99 fire occurring into persistent =
=E2=80=98negative gamma=E2=80=99 momentum overshoot flows,=E2=80=9D he adde=
d. =E2=80=9CUsing the certainty of dealer hedging flows that their orders c=
reate to then amplify and =E2=80=98juice=E2=80=99 the intended directional =
market move =E2=80=A6 before closing-out positions mere hours later by end =
of day.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0

Biblical jet fuel is juicing the flows of fire! Love it. More, please:
=E2=80=9CMost critically as it relates to the outrageous ranges and swings =
this past week in US equities and into the upcoming expiration, it is the s=
taggering amount of (negative) front-delta into Friday=E2=80=99s [options e=
xpiry] that has then needed to be traded on the approach, which is then act=
ing as further shadow-convexity in the market,=E2=80=9D he says.=C2=A0
Ahh so good.
Look. Retail investors on Reddit have been saying for years that there is a=
 viable trading strategy that goes like this:
=09You buy short-dated out-of-the-money call options on a stock.=09This for=
ces options dealers to buy that stock to hedge the options.=09This pushes t=
he stock up.=09As the stock goes up, the dealers need to buy even=C2=A0more=
 of the stock to remain properly hedged.=09This pushes the stock up more.=
=09As the stock goes up, your call options are more valuable.=09Congratulat=
ions, you have created a self-fulfilling trade. You can=E2=80=99t lose.

When I first heard this theory,   I was skeptical. Yes, right, at some leve=
l this is a correct description of how dealers hedge call options: They buy=
 some stock to hedge options that they sell, and then buy more stock as the=
 price goes up. But there is a lot of other stuff going on in the market, a=
nd it seems implausible that retail investors buying stock options would be=
 able to push around the price of a big liquid stock like Tesla Inc. And th=
e effect of dealer hedging goes both ways: If the stock goes=C2=A0down, dea=
lers will sell some of their stock to remain properly hedged, which will pu=
sh it down more. You are not getting a free lunch. The idea that this would=
 just=C2=A0work, as a self-fulfilling automatic money maker, seemed absurd.
I mean, it=C2=A0is=C2=A0absurd, but after January 2021 I am more open to th=
e possibility that it=C2=A0happens. Did retail investors buy a ton of short=
-dated out-of-the-money call options on GameStop Corp.,   causing dealers t=
o hedge by buying a lot of the stock and pushing its price up to insane hei=
ghts? Uh =E2=80=A6=C2=A0  maybe? That=E2=80=99s what they said=C2=A0they di=
d, and the stock sure did go up, though the SEC=E2=80=99s report on the Gam=
eStop phenomenon   mostly discounts this =E2=80=9Cgamma squeeze=E2=80=9D st=
ory.   Others disagree, and all in all I think it is more plausible than it=
 used to be that retail investors can push stock prices around with a lot o=
f options buying. Boy is that not investing advice.
So if you tell me now that professional investors are YOLOing 1-DTE options=
 to push the stock up and automatically make money, =E2=80=9Cusing the cert=
ainty of dealer hedging flows that their orders create to then amplify and =
=E2=80=98juice=E2=80=99 the intended directional market move,=E2=80=9D my r=
eaction is sure, whatever, I guess that=E2=80=99s a thing now.=C2=A0

