<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission=E2=80=
=99s fast-paced rule-making agenda under Chairman Gary Gensler has stretche=
d staff resources, and some officials worry it could increase the risk of l=
awsuits, the agency=E2=80=99s internal watchdog said in a recent report.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In meetings with the SEC=E2=80=99s inspector g=
eneral, managers at the agency expressed concerns about short deadlines for=
 staff to draft proposed rules and for public stakeholders to submit commen=
ts on them, according to the Oct. 13 report. Mr. Gensler=E2=80=99s rule-mak=
ing teams have borrowed staff from across the agency, making it difficult t=
o complete other parts of the SEC=E2=80=99s mission, managers reported.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">While no one identified concrete errors in rul=
e proposals, some managers told the inspector general that =E2=80=9Cthe mor=
e aggressive agenda=E2=80=A6potentially limits the time available for staff=
 research and analysis, and increases litigation risk.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The staff=E2=80=99s complaints are not proof t=
hat Gensler is=C2=A0<em>wrong</em>, but you can see why they=E2=80=99d be a=
nnoyed.</p>
